                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As a five-year veteran of the Test Server, I must argue against your suggestion.
<br />

<br />
First, the thought that people have no incentive to level up characters is incorrect.  As I am involved with the server's leading raid organization and have been friendly with most of the other high-level raiding orgs, I know many people who have multiple (read: <span style="font-style: italic">more</span> than two) level 65 characters.  I myself have a level 65 enchanter and a level 56 necromancer, and I am very much classified as a "casual player."  Indeed, we have someone who levelled a Berzerker to level 65 in just over 3 days /played.
<br />

<br />
Second, the idea of opening up the server to mirror copies of people's "live" characters would destroy the server as we know it, both from an economic standpoint, due to the influx of items and platinum, and from a social standpoint, as thousands of people (who have nothing invested in that particular copy of their character) would have the opportunity to act however they chose without any consequences.  I'm not saying that all would act that way, but more than enough certainly would.
<br />

<br />
We have a dedicated testing crew, people who have been working with the developers for over four years, and in some cases, over five.  A working relationship of trust and partnership has been built up over that time, something that cannot be traded for sheer numbers.  This testing crew works intimately with the developers to tune raid targets and other specific circumstances.
<br />

<br />
Opening up the Test Server to the floodgates of unaccountable level 65 characters would be a vast, vast mistake.
<br />

<br />
Also, this suggestion has been brought up in the past, and always ignored.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
